description.title: Sphynx cat
description.content: The Sphynx cat (pronounced SFYNGKS, /ˈsfɪŋks/) is a breed of cat known for its lack of fur. Hairlessness in cats is a naturally occurring genetic mutation, and the Sphynx was developed through selective breeding of these animals, starting in the 1960s.
